{
  "texts": [
    "To harness the power of LLMs and address the two aforementioned concerns, CodeTailor aims to achieve two high-level goals: generate correct code solutions using LLMs in real-time, and establish a programming support system that encourages engagement and active learning.",
    "Scaffolding student programmingPrevious research on assisting students while learning programming has investigated different scaffolding methods.",
    "Scaffolding, as defined by Bruner [7], involves providing support to students to learn a skill beyond their current level.",
    "One common approach to timely assistance is detailed hints based on the students' current code state, aiming to help students progress toward a correct solution [31,39,50,63].",
    "A more comprehensive scaffolding resource could be a library of code examples for students to refer to during practice [61]."
  ]
}